title: Bouillabaisse (mediterranean Fish Soup)
summary: Bouillabaisse (mediterranean Fish Soup) might be just the main course you are searching for. One serving contains 671 calories, 67g of protein, and 21g of fat. For $6.43 per serving, this recipe covers 47% of your daily requirements of vitamins and minerals. This recipe serves 8. Autumn will be even more special with this recipe. It is a good option if you're following a dairy free and pescatarian diet. 13 people have tried and liked this recipe. If you have fennel stalk, onion, egg yolks, and a few other ingredients on hand, you can make it. To use up the salt you could follow this main course with the Apple Turnovers Recipe as a dessert. Taking all factors into account, this recipe earns a spoonacular score of 94%, which is excellent. Try My simplified Fish Bouillabaisse — Ma bouillabaisse version simplifiée, Mediterranean Fish Soup, and Chunky Mediterranean fish soup for similar recipes.

winePairing.pairingText: Fish can be paired with Pinot Grigio, Gruener Veltliner, and Pinot Noir. Fish is as diverse as wine, so it's hard to pick wines that go with every fish. A crisp white wine, such as a pinot grigio or Grüner Veltliner, will suit any delicately flavored white fish. Meaty, strongly flavored fish such as salmon and tuna can even handle a light red wine, such as a pinot noir. The Prophecy Pinot Grigio with a 4 out of 5 star rating seems like a good match. It costs about 10 dollars per bottle.

productMatches.title: Prophecy Pinot Grigio
productMatches.description: The Pinot Grigio offers the best of the high altitude delle Venezie region. Flavors of light citrus, tropical fruit, and mineral notes offer crisp, refreshment and are complemented by delicate floral aromas.
